                     <decoNote type="miniature">
                        <locus from="1v" to="2r"/>Double-page court scene within a splendid illuminated border and decorated margins. On 1v is<persName key="http://lccn.loc.gov/n80034374">Shah 'Abbas</persName>enthroned with courtiers and musicians; on 2r are courtiers and ladies, together with Turkish, Indian and European ambassadors, all on a terrace with a garden behind red railings. Some of the faces slightly blackened. Each half<dimensions type="written" unit="cm">
                           <height>18.5</height>
                           <width>11</width>
                        </dimensions>.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature">
                        <locus from="413v" to="414r"/>Double-page miniature of a royal hunt with a splendid illuminated border and margins. On 413v the prince, evidently intended for<persName key="http://lccn.loc.gov/n80034374">Shah 'Abbas</persName>, is seated under a tree inspecting the bag. He is surrounded by attendantswith hawks and hunting cheetahs. On 414r the hunt is in progress, the quarry flown, leopard, lion, wild pig and gazelle. Each half<dimensions type="written" unit="cm">
                           <height>18.5</height>
                           <width>11</width>
                        </dimensions>.</decoNote>
